# This file contains a list of files that will be excluded from Shopify CLI
# operations such as push, pull, dev, etc.
#
# Examples:
#
# Ignore a specific file:
#   templates/product.json
#
# Ignore templates with a wildcard pattern:
#   templates/*.json
#
# Ignore templates and sections with a regular expression:
#   /(templates|sections)/.*\.json/

# Ignore CLI temp files (Windows hot-reload artefacts)
*.tmp.*
# Ignore atomic-save / `sed -i` temp files (e.g. sections/sed4tSofo) — extensionless
# files an editor or sed writes mid-save. The dev/push watcher catches them and
# fails with "Must have a .liquid file extension". Real theme files always have one.
/(sections|snippets|templates|layout|locales|config|assets|blocks)/[^.]+$/
claudeinfo.txt
commands.txt
assets/critical.source.css
package.json
package-lock.json
